  "body": "I noticed that Status actually somehow integrates itself with web3 transactions on the browser that is set as the default browser (atleast on Android).\r\n\r\nSo since ie. idex.market shows the UI without the need for a connection, so no Mist/Metamask/Status required to view the whole site, if i would go to the Wallet and enter an amount and hit Deposit, a transaction confirmation screen (silently) opens up in Status as a pending transaction asking for a password, without the need for any interaction done in Status. So for a site like mkr.market it doesn't work, since they don't show anything without the connection, but this implies that any web site could just add code on a regular web page for transactions and it would work with Status.\r\n\r\nI tested this with Opera and Chrome on Android, works on both as long as that browser is set as the default browser.",
